Propose intersections: moments where beats from DIFFERENT dilemmas could share one
scene. The beats stay separate and keep advancing their own dilemmas — an
intersection only declares "these belong in the same room at the same time", so the
interleaver places them adjacently and a later stage may merge them into one passage.
Good intersections braid the storylines: the subplot's business happens *inside* the
backbone's tension instead of alternating politely with it.

VISION: {{ vision.genre }}, {{ vision.tone }}.

SHARED BEATS (experienced by every player; only these may intersect — a locked
storyline is a fork-less subplot on every playthrough, so its beats qualify too):
{% for d in dilemmas %}
- {{ d.dilemma.id }} ({{ d.dilemma.role }}{% if d.locked %}, locked storyline{% endif %}): {{ d.dilemma.question }}
{% for b in d.beats %}
  - {{ b.id }} — {{ b.summary }} (entities: {{ b.entities | join(", ") }})
{% if b.flexibility %}
    flexibility: {{ b.flexibility }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

REQUIREMENTS:
- Each group: >=2 members, every member from a DIFFERENT dilemma, taken only from
  the shared beats listed above. No beat may appear in two groups.
- Only propose a group when the co-occurrence is natural — shared entities, shared
  place, or an explicit flexibility note. Forced intersections read as coincidence.
- Zero groups is a valid answer: {"groups": []}.
- Group ids: intersection:slug. Set location to the shared place's entity id when
  one anchors the scene; give a one-sentence rationale.
